@remark *** OBJECT MENU HELP ***

@node MAIN "Menus:  Object"

@{FG Highlight}Object:@{FG Text}
@{code}
@{" Style Tags...       " link TAGS}  Edit or set object styles.

@{" Edit...             " link EDIT}  Edit the coordinates of the selected object(s).
@{" Information...      " link INFO}  View information on an object(s).
@{" Line/Fill...        " link LIFI}  Set the line/fill style/color for the selected object(s).
@{" Trapping...         " link TRAP}  Set trapping for the selected object(s).

@{" Text Wrap...        " link WRAP}  Set text runaround for the selected object(s).
@{" Text Anchor...      " link ANCH}  Set the position of an anchored object.
@{" Text Frame          " link FRAM}  Toggle the text frame status of an object.

@{" Duplicate           " link DUPE}  Duplicate the selected object(s).
@{" Transform...        " link TRAN}  Transform the selected object(s).
@{" Rotate...           " link ROTA}  Rotate the selected object(s).
@{" Move...             " link MOVE}  Move the selected object(s) a set amount.
@{" Move to Page...     " link MVPG}  Move selected object(s) to another page.
@{" Align...            " link ALIN}  Align the selected object(s).
@{" Distribute...       " link DIST}  Space out the selected object(s)

@{" Split Paths         " link SPLT}  Split a composite object into separate paths.
@{" Merge Paths         " link MERG}  Merge separate paths into a composite object.

@{" Group               " link GRUP}  Group selected objects.
@{" Ungroup             " link UNGP}  Ungroup a group into separate objects.
@{" Lock                " link LOCK}  Lock selected object(s) in place.
@{" Unlock              " link UNLK}  Unlock selected object(s).

@{" Make Drawing        " link MKDR}  Create a new drawing.
@{" Dissolve Drawing    " link DIDR}  Dissolve a drawing into its component parts.
@{" Add to Drawing      " link ADDR}  Add selected object(s) to the selected drawing.

@{" Bring to Front      " link FRON}  Move selected object(s) to the top of the stack.
@{" Bring Forward       " link FRON}  Move selected object(s) one level forward in the stack.
@{" Send to Back        " link BACK}  Move selected object(s) to the bottom of the stack.
@{" Send Backward       " link BACK}  Move selected object(s) one level forward
@{body}
@{body}
